{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"7dc58b42-e048-47e6-98c8-a18914f4a27c","content":"**Use `dotnet-trace`** — it's the simplest option for .NET 8 CPU profiling. No install beyond the .NET SDK tools.\n\n### Setup (one-time)\n```powershell\ndotnet tool install --global dotnet-trace\n```\n\n### Collect a 30-second CPU trace\n```powershell\n# Find your process ID\ndotnet-trace ps\n\n# Collect with the cpu-sampling profile\ndotnet-trace collect -p <PID> --profile cpu-sampling --duration 00:00:30\n```\n\nThis writes a `.nettrace` file you can open in **Visual Studio** (Diagnostics Hub) or **PerfView**.\n\n### Alternative: PerfView (deeper analysis)\nIf you need kernel-level call stacks (driver/OS overhead, context switches):\n\n```powershell\n# Download from https://github.com/microsoft/perfview/releases\nPerfView.exe collect -Duration:30 -CircularMB:500\n```\n\nPerfView uses ETW and gives richer data but has a steeper learning curve.\n\n### Quick recommendation\n\n| Scenario | Tool |\n|---|---|\n| App-level hot path (most cases) | `dotnet-trace` |\n| Kernel + app mixed stacks | PerfView |\n| Production w/ minimal overhead | `dotnet-monitor` |\n\nStart with `dotnet-trace` — it's usually enough to identify the hot method.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"8fe23d17-7279-4523-9a8d-1d1c77011a12","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking for guidance on collecting a CPU trace for a .NET 8 service on Windows Server. This is a knowledge/advice question, not a code task. I should provide a concise, practical answer.\n\nThe best tool for this is `dotnet-trace` or PerfView. For CPU specifically, `dotnet-trace` with the cpu-sampling profile is the simplest approach, but PerfView gives richer ETW-based data. Since they have admin access on Windows, PerfView is the gold standard for CPU investigations on Windows.\n\nLet me give a concise answer.","outputTokens":479,"requestId":"2159:3AA73:5D2E951:65EFA73:69F00C93"},"id":"9bef455f-254d-48c7-8fde-5c827795c357","timestamp":"2026-04-28T01:25:52.849Z","parentId":"6977c31a-b6cc-45ab-850c-b192cea1dea8"}
